description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;STEP Pharmacists- Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;University Hospital Lewisham and Queen Elizabeth Hospital, Woolwich&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen at Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust for pharmacists with drive and ability to become part of the dynamic pharmacy team. You will work in a supportive environment with training opportunities, to build your foundation skills and develop your expertise. We have positions available at both hospital sites, some positions are to start as soon as able and others we are recruiting in advance to start in March 2021 at the latest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The clinical pharmacy service to the wards is well established and provides high quality care across a variety of specialties. Joining a team of experienced pharmacists and technicians you will work as part of the multidisciplinary team to deliver a patient focused clinical pharmacy service to the wards. You will have the opportunity to rotate through a variety of specialities within Lewisham and Queen Elizabeth Hospital and be offered opportunities to apply for placements as part of the STEP programme at other hospitals in South East London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The programme provides competency based training, education and experience over three years to equip pharmacists with the skills and knowledge to provide the highest quality professional care and progress their careers. The post requires a highly motivated pharmacist with excellent communication, interpersonal and time management skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please view our FAQ or please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
